# Code Conventions

## WordPress Development
- Follow WordPress Coding Standards (PHPCS) — 4-space indent, no tabs
- Prefix every custom PHP function/class with `zs_`
- Escape all outputs (esc_html, esc_attr, wp_kses_post)
- Sanitize all inputs (sanitize_text_field, absint, etc.)
- Use core APIs & hooks instead of editing plugin/core files
- Prefer actions/filters over template hacks
- Ensure PHP 8.1 compatibility
- Declare strict types when useful

## HTML Structure
- HTML5 doctype is used across all pages
- Language is set to Brazilian Portuguese (`lang="pt-BR"`)
- UTF-8 character encoding
- Responsive viewport meta tag
- Semantic HTML elements (`header`, `main`, `footer`, `section`, `article`)
- Gutenberg-compatible markup
- Add theme support for align-wide

## CSS Organization
- BEM (Block Element Modifier) methodology for class naming
- Example: `.product-card__image-container`, `.product-card__button`
- Responsive design using media queries
- CSS variables for consistent theming
- No inline <style> blocks
- Migrate all styles to SCSS/JS files
- Preserve existing CSS structure unless necessary to change

## Asset Management
- Register & version assets with wp_enqueue_*
- Supply dependency arrays for all assets
- Use filemtime() for cache-busting
- Place block patterns in /patterns/ with block.json

## JavaScript & Internationalization
- Localize scripts via wp_set_script_translations / wp.i18n
- Make all strings translation-ready
- Use __() or _x() for all text strings
- Implement WordPress search in main.js (final step)
- Verify nonce with check_ajax_referer() for AJAX
- Die with wp_send_json_* for AJAX responses
- Never output debug code in production

## Accessibility
- ARIA labels and roles are used for better accessibility
- Example: `role="search"`, `aria-label="Toggle menu"`
- Semantic HTML structure
- Alt text for images
- Adhere to WCAG 2.1 AA standards

## External Dependencies
- Font Awesome 6.5.1 for icons
- Google Fonts (Arimo font family)
- Custom JavaScript in `assets/js/main.js`
- WooCommerce 9.x
- Contact Form 7

## Component Structure
- Header with navigation and search
- Product cards with consistent structure
- Footer with social media, institutional links, and contact information
- Slider components with navigation controls
